The paper proposes a novel framework for predicting dynamic Origin-Destination (O-D) demand matrices using graph neural networks and Kalman filter. This involves the use of deep learning techniques for spatial-temporal prediction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with network optimization and traffic flow analysis, which can be categorized under neural networks (cs.NE) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the use of statistical methods such as Kalman filter, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
